other_tests.findings: Large fluid-filled appendix with a large appendicolith near the base measuring approximately 1.6 x 0.6 cm. No evidence of perforation or adjacent abscess formation. Multiple small retroperitoneal and mesenteric lymph nodes, none meet CT criteria for pathologic enlargement. Mild dilatation of the central intrahepatic biliary ducts.
Rectum and bladder are within normal limits. An IUD is seen within the uterus, appropriately positioned. There is a small amount of free fluid.
